"Sidebottom H., Franklin J.","The atmospheric fate and impact of hydrochlorofluorocarbons and chlorinated solvents",1996,"Pure and Applied Chemistry","68","9",,"1757","1769",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0000171814&partnerID=40&md5=948cce74693b7b408a11a801b0b4732d","Department of Chemistry, University College Dublin, Belfleld, Dublin 4, Ireland; Alternative Fluorocarbons E., West Tower, 1333 H Street NW, Washington, DC, United States","Sidebottom, H., Department of Chemistry, University College Dublin, Belfleld, Dublin 4, Ireland; Franklin, J., Alternative Fluorocarbons E., West Tower, 1333 H Street NW, Washington, DC, United States","A very considerable body of data pertaining to the atmospheric behaviour of hydrochlorofluorocarbons (HCFCs) and chlorinated solvents is now available and leads to the following conclusions: (a) these compounds, with the exception of 1,1,1 -trichloroethane, make a small or insignificant contribution to stratospheric ozone depletion, global warming, 'photo-chemical smog', 'acid rain', or chloride and fluoride levels in precipitation; (b) it seems highly unlikely that the chlorinated solvents degrade in the atmosphere to give chloroacetic acids as major products, as has often been claimed in the literature.",,,,,,,,"Alternative Fluorocarbons Environmental Acceptability Study (1995) Production, Sales and Atmospheric Release of Fluoro-carbons through 1994, , AFEAS, The West Tower - Suite 400,1333 H Street NW, Washington DC 20005, USA; McCulloch, A., Midgley, P.M., (1996) Atmos. Environ., 30 (4), pp. 601-608; Midgley, P.M., McCulloch, A., (1995) Atmos. Environ., 29 (14), pp. 1601-1608; (1995) Global Ozone Research and Monitoring Project - Report No. 37, Scientific Assessment of Ozone Depletion: 1994, , WMO, Geneva; Wallington, T.J., Schneider, W.F., Worsnop, D.R., Nielsen, O.J., Sehested, J., DeBruyn, W.J., Shorter, J.A., (1994) Environ. Sci. Technol., 28 (7), pp. 320A-326A; Midgley, P.M., (1995) Volatile Organic Co